James assigned Goulder & Schein (2013) for a class on Climate Change Economics. The paper compares carbon taxes, cap and trade, and hybrid systems, highlighting the advantages of exogenous emissions pricing. Key points include preventing price volatility, reducing policy errors, avoiding large wealth transfers, and facilitating easier international policy linkage. To assess student comprehension, multiple-choice questions were suggested covering topics like policy advantages, drawbacks, and design considerations, ensuring understanding of the nuanced comparisons between policy tools.
